-- Japanese Bought Net 309.9 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2013-05-09T23:53:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-09/japanese-bought-net-309-9-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended May 3 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 309.9 billion yen ($3.1 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 28 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 54.9 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 283.1 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 267 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 26.2 billion yen in stocks, and sold 123.8 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 117
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
